  "body": "When utilizing RPC tracing methods such as trace_block, all the relevant data is readily available in the corresponding trie log. Besu can retrieve data from the trie logs, thereby reducing the need for extensive disk access. The trie log can be directly accessed in memory, particularly in a Bonsai implementation for the most recent 512 blocks, or it can be sourced from the disk.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, if a node lacks the complete trie logs, another solution could be to acquire the trie log via P2P from other Besu nodes, through a torrent, or other similar methods.\r\n\r\n",
